============================================================
- Urine culture (sent Day 1 — growth of >10^5 CFU Escherichia coli reported Day 6;
  sensitivities: sensitive to trimethoprim, nitrofurantoin, cephalexin; treated with
  3-day course trimethoprim 300mg nocte — completed Day 8. GP to ensure follow-up urine
  if symptoms persist.)
- Thyroid antibodies (sent to rule out autoimmune thyroid disease given borderline TSH
  trend over past 12 months; result pending — GP to follow up)
- Right-sided pleural effusion: to be re-evaluated with chest X-ray at GP follow-up;
  may require repeat imaging or thoracentesis if not resolved with diuresis
